@startuml Sequence_Fabric_Management

actor Admin
participant "Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Backend API" as API
database "Database" as DB
actor Customer

== Admin Adds Fabric ==

Admin -> Frontend: Access Fabric Management
Frontend -> API: GET /api/fabrics
API -> DB: Fetch all fabrics
DB --> API: Fabrics list
API --> Frontend: Fabrics data
Frontend --> Admin: Display fabrics

Admin -> Frontend: Add New Fabric
Frontend --> Admin: Display fabric form

Admin -> Frontend: Fill Fabric Details\n(name, material, color, price, stock, category)
Frontend -> Frontend: Validate form

Admin -> Frontend: Submit Fabric
Frontend -> API: POST /api/fabrics\n(fabric details, createdBy)
API -> DB: Create fabric
DB --> API: Fabric created

API --> Frontend: Fabric created
Frontend --> Admin: Success message\n+ Fabric list updated

== Admin Updates Fabric Stock ==

Admin -> Frontend: Select Fabric
Frontend -> API: GET /api/fabrics/:id
API -> DB: Fetch fabric
DB --> API: Fabric details
API --> Frontend: Fabric data
Frontend --> Admin: Display fabric details

Admin -> Frontend: Update Stock\n(new stock quantity)
Frontend -> API: PUT /api/fabrics/:id\n(stock = newQuantity)
API -> DB: Update fabric stock
DB --> API: Fabric updated

API --> Frontend: Stock updated
Frontend --> Admin: Success message

== Customer Browses Fabrics ==

Customer -> Frontend: Browse Fabrics
Frontend -> API: GET /api/fabrics?isActive=true
API -> DB: Fetch active fabrics
DB --> API: Active fabrics list
API --> Frontend: Fabrics data
Frontend --> Customer: Display fabric catalog

Customer -> Frontend: View Fabric Details
Frontend -> API: GET /api/fabrics/:id
API -> DB: Fetch fabric details
DB --> API: Fabric details
API --> Frontend: Fabric data
Frontend --> Customer: Display fabric details\n(images, price, stock, description)

== Fabric Stock Check During Order ==

Customer -> Frontend: Place Order with Fabric
Frontend -> API: POST /api/orders\n(fabricId, quantity)
API -> DB: Check fabric stock
DB --> API: Fabric (stock = currentStock)

alt Sufficient Stock
  API -> DB: Update fabric\n(stock = stock - quantity)
  DB --> API: Stock reduced
  
  API -> DB: Create order
  DB --> API: Order created
  
  API --> Frontend: Order created
  Frontend --> Customer: Order confirmation
  
else Insufficient Stock
  API --> Frontend: Error: Insufficient stock
  Frontend --> Customer: Error message\n"Stock not available"
end

== Low Stock Alert ==

DB -> API: Check low stock fabrics
API -> DB: Query fabrics\n(stock <= lowStockThreshold)
DB --> API: Low stock fabrics

API -> DB: Create notification for admin
DB --> API: Notification created

DB -> Admin: Notification: "Low stock alert"

note right of DB
  Fabric Fields:
  - name, material, color
  - price, stock, category
  - isActive, lowStockThreshold
end note

@enduml


